zab-aAbN 
A seller of zabiyb [or raisins]; 
as also zabiybiI-N↓. (Ḳ.)

[Hence,] said of the sidor [or lote-tree], (Ṣ, A, Ḳ,) ‡ It blossomed; (Ṣ, Ḳ, TA;) i. e. (TA) it put forth a white produce like the froth, or foam, upon water. (A, TA.) 
And, said of the qataAdi [or tragacantha], † It put forth its leaf (xuwSap), and its wood, or branch, became strong, or hard, and its rind, or outer covering, coalesced, and it blossomed; 
as also zb-d↓. (L.)

