Q. 4. AizolaEab-a, (Ḳ,) 
inf. n. AizoliEobaAbN, (Ṣ in art. zEb,) said of a torrent, It was, or became, copious, and impelled in its several parts, or portions, by the impetus of one part, or portion, acting upon another. (Ṣ, Ḳ.) Accord. to the Ṣ, and AḤei, the l is augmentative; 
[as it is said with equal reason to be in Aizolagab-a;] but accord. to the Ḳ, it is radical, and therefore this is its proper place, not art. zEb. (TA.)

