aor. _i {yazoliqu}, 
inf. n. zaloqN, (Ṣ,) He shaved his head; 
as also Azlqhu↓; 
and zl-qhu↓, (Ṣ, Ḳ,) inf. n. tazoliyqN: (Ṣ:) IB says that, accord. to ʼAlee Ibn-Hamzeh, it is only zabaqahu, with b; and that Alz-aboqu means the plucking out; not the shaving: but accord. to Fr, one says of him who has shaved his head qd zlqh, 
[whether with or without teshdeed is not shown,] and Azlqh. (TA.)

