(Ṣ, O, Ḳ; [in this sense correctly said in the Ḳ to be like kitaAbN;]) 
a certain ornament for women, (JK, Ibn-ʼAbbád, O,) of silver. (Ibn-ʼAbbád, O.)

1. zanaA, 
[aor. yazonuw,] inf. n. zunuw-N, It was, or became, strait, or narrow; 
a dial. var. of zanaOa; (ISd, Ḳ, TA;) said of a place. (TA.)

hom.sense:
1. zahida fiyhi, (Ṣ, A, Mgh, Mṣb, Ḳ,) and Eanohu, (Ṣ, Mgh, Mṣb,) 
aor. _a {yazohadu}; (Ṣ, Ḳ;) [the most usual form of the verb;] and zahada, 
aor. _a {yazohadu}; (Ṣ, Mṣb, Ḳ;) which is the most approved form, though MF says otherwise; (TA;) and zahuda, 
aor. _u {yazohudu}; (Th, Ḳ;) inf. n. zuhodN and zahaAdapN (Ṣ, Mgh, Mṣb, Ḳ) and zahodN; (Sb, TA;) He abstained from it; 
[meaning, from something that would gratify the passions or senses;] relinquished it; forsook it; shunned, or avoided, it; did not desire it; (Ṣ, A, Mgh, Mṣb, Ḳ;) contr. of ragiba [i. e. of ragiba fiyhi], (Ṣ, Ḳ,) and i. q. ragiba Eanohu, (A, Mgh,) and lamo yuridohu, (Mgh,) and tarakahu and OaEoraDa Eanohu: (Mṣb:) or he abstained from it, meaning a thing of the lawfulness of which he was sure, so far as to take the least that was sufficient thereof, leaving the rest to God: (MF:) or zahaAdapN relates only to worldly things; and zuhodN, to matters of religion: (Kh, Mṣb, Ḳ:) or both signify the exercising oneself in the service of God, or in acts of devotion; 
as also tazah-udN↓: (KL:) he who makes a difference between zahida fiyhi and zahida Eanohu errs. (Mgh.)

